snippet.textDisplay: My 9 year old daughter found a largish (suspected) mako shark tooth in the shallows near The Pass in Byron Bay. She was wearing the goggles and I was dragging her around and she suddenly said dad I think I saw a shark tooth. My reaction was Oh no, you did not. Must have been a piece of shell. I have never found or even heard of anyone finding a shark tooth in the shallows or on the beach. But she looked around a bit more and found it again. We showed a ranger and he was also very impressed. It is about an inch long and quite narrow from base to tip.
